							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/laurenfrancissharma/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Francis-Sharma-Lauren-credit-Anna-Carson-DeWitt-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Francis-Sharma-Lauren-credit-Anna-Carson-DeWitt-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Lauren Francis-Sharma" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/laurenfrancissharma/">Lauren Francis-Sharma</a></h6>
										Lauren Francis-Sharma is also the author of the critically acclaimed novel <em>’Til the Well Runs Dry</em>. She resides near Washington, DC with her husband and two children and is the assistant director of the Bread Loaf Writers’ Conference.																			</div>
